verses.text: I will sing of the mercies of the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* for ever : with my mouth will I make known thy faithfulness to all generations.\f + \fr 89.1 \ft Maschil…: or, A Psalm for Ethan the Ezrahite, to give instruction\f*\f + \fr 89.1 \ft to all…: Heb. to generation and generation\f* \q1
For I have said , Mercy shall be built up for ever : thy faithfulness shalt thou establish in the very heavens. \q1
I have made a covenant with my chosen , I have sworn unto David my servant , \q1
Thy seed will I establish for ever , and build up thy throne to all generations. Selah. \b \q1
And the heavens shall praise thy wonders , O \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*: thy faithfulness also in the congregation of the saints. \q1

For who in the heaven can be compared unto the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d*? \add who\add* among the sons of the mighty can be likened unto the 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d*? \q1
God is greatly to be feared in the assembly of the saints , and to be had in reverence of all \add them that are\add* about him. \q1

O 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*
d* God of hosts , who \add is\add* a strong 
d \+w LORD|strong="H3050"\+w*
d* like unto thee? or to thy faithfulness round about thee? \q1
Thou rulest the raging of the sea : when the waves thereof arise , thou stillest them. \q1

Thou hast broken Rahab in pieces , as one that is slain ; thou hast scattered thine enemies with thy strong arm.\f + \fr 89.10 \ft Rahab: or, Egypt\f*\f + \fr 89.10 \ft thy…: Heb. the arm of thy strength\f* \q1

The heavens \add are\add* thine, the earth also \add is\add* thine: \add as for\add* the world and the fulness thereof, thou hast founded them.\f + \fr 89.11 \ft the fulness…: or, all it containeth\f* \q1
The north and the south thou hast created them: Tabor and Hermon shall rejoice in thy name. \q1
Thou hast a mighty arm : strong is thy hand , \add and\add* high is thy right hand.\f + \fr 89.13 \ft a…: Heb. an arm with might\f* \q1
Justice and judgment \add are\add* the habitation of thy throne : mercy and truth shall go before thy face.\f + \fr 89.14 \ft habitation: or, establishment\f* \b \q1
Blessed \add is\add* the people that know the joyful sound : they shall walk , O \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*, in the light of thy countenance. \q1
In thy name shall they rejoice all the day : and in thy righteousness shall they be exalted. \q1
For thou \add art\add* the glory of their strength : and in thy favour our horn shall be exalted. \q1

For the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* \add is\add* our defence ; and the Holy One of Israel \add is\add* our king.\f + \fr 89.18 \ft the \+nd LORD\+nd*…: or, our shield is of the \+nd LORD\+nd*, and our king is of the Holy One of Israel\f* \b \q1
Then thou spakest in vision to thy holy one , and saidst , I have laid help upon \add one that is\add* mighty ; I have exalted \add one\add* chosen out of the people. \q1
I have found David my servant ; with my holy oil have I anointed him: \q1
With whom my hand shall be established : mine arm also shall strengthen him. \q1
The enemy shall not exact upon him; nor the son of wickedness afflict him. \q1
And I will beat down his foes before his face , and plague them that hate him. \q1
But my faithfulness and my mercy \add shall be\add* with him: and in my name shall his horn be exalted. \q1
I will set his hand also in the sea , and his right hand in the rivers. \q1
He shall cry unto me, Thou \add art\add* my father , my God , and the rock of my salvation. \q1
Also I will make him \add my\add* firstborn , higher than the kings of the earth. \q1
My mercy will I keep for him for evermore , and my covenant shall stand fast with him. \q1
His seed also will I make \add to endure\add* for ever , and his throne as the days of heaven. \q1
If his children forsake my law , and walk not in my judgments ; \q1
If they break my statutes , and keep not my commandments ;\f + \fr 89.31 \ft break: Heb. profane\f* \q1
Then will I visit their transgression with the rod , and their iniquity with stripes. \q1

Nevertheless my lovingkindness will I not utterly take from him, nor suffer my faithfulness to fail.\f + \fr 89.33 \ft will…: Heb. I will not make void from him\f*\f + \fr 89.33 \ft to fail: Heb. to lie\f* \q1
My covenant will I not break , nor alter the thing that is gone out of my lips. \q1
Once have I sworn by my holiness that I will not lie unto David.\f + \fr 89.35 \ft that…: Heb. if I lie\f* \q1
His seed shall endure for ever , and his throne as the sun before me. \q1
It shall be established for ever as the moon , and \add as\add* a faithful witness in heaven. Selah. \b \q1
But thou hast cast off and abhorred , thou hast been wroth with thine anointed. \q1
Thou hast made void the covenant of thy servant : thou hast profaned his crown \add by casting it\add* to the ground. \q1
Thou hast broken down all his hedges ; thou hast brought his strong holds to ruin. \q1
All that pass by the way spoil him: he is a reproach to his neighbours. \q1
Thou hast set up the right hand of his adversaries ; thou hast made all his enemies to rejoice. \q1
Thou hast also turned the edge of his sword , and hast not made him to stand in the battle. \q1
Thou hast made his glory to cease , and cast his throne down to the ground.\f + \fr 89.44 \ft glory: Heb. brightness\f* \q1
The days of his youth hast thou shortened : thou hast covered him with shame. Selah. \q1
How long, \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*? wilt thou hide thyself for ever ? shall thy wrath burn like fire ? \q1
Remember how short my time is: wherefore hast thou made all men in vain ? \q1
What man \add is he that\add* liveth , and shall not see death ? shall he deliver his soul from the hand of the grave ? Selah. \q1
Lord , where \add are\add* thy former lovingkindnesses , \add which\add* thou swarest unto David in thy truth ? \q1
Remember , Lord , the reproach of thy servants ; \add how\add* I do bear in my bosom \add the reproach of\add* all the mighty people ; \q1
Wherewith thine enemies have reproached , O \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd*; wherewith they have reproached the footsteps of thine anointed. \q1
Blessed \add be\add* the \nd \+w LORD|strong="H3068"\+w*\nd* for evermore. Amen , and Amen.
